headline: Exploring 3 High Growth Tech Stocks In The US Market
summary: As the U.S. market navigates a period of retreat from record highs, with tech stocks experiencing notable declines, investors are closely monitoring key indices like the S&P 500 and Dow Jones Industrial Average for signs of broader economic trends. Amidst this backdrop, identifying high growth tech stocks requires a keen eye on companies that demonstrate resilience and adaptability in an evolving economic landscape.

headline: Britain's Kainos jumps on upbeat annual outlook
summary: Kainos, a partner of U.S. software firm Workday, said its Workday products division — which builds applications used within the platform — continued to grow and passed the $100 million annual recurring revenue milestone in July.  Kainos said momentum was picking up across its divisions, with new projects prompting it to hire more staff and make greater short-term use of contractors.
